Claude for Legal Turkish — Maaty Fork
======================================

This is `memirutku/claude-for-legal-turkish-maaty`, a Maaty-maintained fork of:

    Direct upstream:   https://github.com/ZekaiSuni/claude-for-legal-turkish
    Direct upstream author: ZekaiSuni (https://github.com/ZekaiSuni)

    Original upstream: https://github.com/anthropics/claude-for-legal
    Original author:   Anthropic (https://github.com/anthropics)

    License: Apache License, Version 2.0 (see LICENSE)


About the upstream chain
------------------------

The original "Claude for Legal" plugin collection was developed and open-
sourced by Anthropic under Apache 2.0. ZekaiSuni then adapted the entire
plugin set for Turkish law (TBK, TTK, KVKK, HMK, İK, SPK, vs.) — this is
the major Turkish-adaptation work that gives this codebase its value.

Maaty's fork pulls from ZekaiSuni's Turkish adaptation and adds project-
specific packaging for Maaty's production deployment. All upstream
attribution and copyright notices are preserved unchanged.


Maaty Modifications (this fork)
-------------------------------

Maaty's intended additions to the ZekaiSuni base are **packaging and
service infrastructure**, not skill-content changes:

* `legal_plugins/` (planned, Faz 6.1+)
    FastAPI service that loads skill manifests from this repo and exposes
    HTTP endpoints (`GET /skills`, `POST /skills/{id}/invoke` with SSE
    streaming). The service uses Maaty's BYOK flow — every invoke request
    carries a per-user `X-AI-Provider`/`X-AI-Model`/`X-AI-Key` header,
    decrypted by Maaty backend. No long-lived API keys live in this
    container.

* `Dockerfile` + `.github/workflows/docker-publish.yml` (planned, Faz 6.1+)
    Container image build that publishes to
    `ghcr.io/memirutku/claude-for-legal-turkish-maaty` for Maaty's prod
    deploy.

* `NOTICE`, `README.md` fork-attribution header (this commit)
    Provenance documentation and prominent fork attribution at the top
    of the README so visitors see the upstream chain immediately.

**Skill content (markdown manifests, instructions, output examples) is
NOT modified** in the initial Maaty fork — ZekaiSuni's Turkish-adapted
skills are used as-is. If Maaty later needs provider-specific prompt
tuning (e.g. Gemini vs. Claude variants), those changes will live in
clearly-marked Maaty-only files (`instructions-gemini.md`) without
touching upstream files.


Sync With Upstreams
-------------------

Maaty periodically pulls updates from both upstream sources:

1. **ZekaiSuni/claude-for-legal-turkish** — primary base. Maaty rebases
   its packaging commits onto fresh ZekaiSuni HEAD.

2. **anthropics/claude-for-legal** — original upstream. When Anthropic
   ships new skills, the typical path is ZekaiSuni adapting them for
   Turkish law first, then Maaty pulling via path 1. If urgent, Maaty
   may pull directly and submit a TR-adaptation PR to ZekaiSuni.

See `docs/mcp-cli/upstream_sources.md` (in the Maaty main repo) for the
current commit SHAs being tracked.


